We're setting up the necessary variables and types. `ι` is the type of indices, `Ω` is the type of outcomes, `m` is the measurable space structure on `Ω`, `X` and `Y` are random variables (functions from `Ω` to sets of indices), `s` and `u` are sets of indices, `i` and `j` are specific indices, `p` and `q` are probability values, and `P` is the probability measure on `Ω`.

